<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Help &amp; How-To — AgentHubTX</title>
<style>
  :root{
    --navy:#0C3057;
    --navy-deep:#082140;
    --gold:#C8922A;
    --gold-light:#E4B968;
    --cream:#F4F1EA;
    --ink:#1C2530;
    --line:#D9D2C2;
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box;}
  body{
    margin:0;
    background:var(--cream);
    color:var(--ink);
    font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  }
  .page{
    max-width:820px;
    margin:0 auto;
    padding:44px 36px 70px;
  }
  .eyebrow{
    text-transform:uppercase;
    letter-spacing:.12em;
    font-size:11.5px;
    color:var(--gold);
    font-weight:700;
    margin-bottom:10px;
  }
  h1{
    font-family:Georgia, serif;
    color:var(--navy);
    font-size:30px;
    margin:0 0 10px;
  }
  .intro{
    font-size:14.5px;
    color:#4a4436;
    max-width:600px;
    line-height:1.55;
    margin-bottom:14px;
  }
  .search-hint{
    font-size:12.5px;
    color:#8a8271;
    margin-bottom:32px;
    font-style:italic;
  }
  .group-title{
    font-family:Georgia, serif;
    color:var(--navy);
    font-size:14px;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    letter-spacing:.06em;
    margin:36px 0 12px;
    padding-bottom:8px;
    border-bottom:2px solid var(--gold);
  }
  details{
    background:#fff;
    border:1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius:6px;
    margin-bottom:10px;
    overflow:hidden;
    scroll-margin-top:24px;
  }
  details.highlight{
    border-color:var(--gold);
    box-shadow:0 0 0 2px var(--gold-light);
  }
  summary{
    list-style:none;
    cursor:pointer;
    padding:16px 18px;
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    justify-content:space-between;
    gap:12px;
  }
  summary::-webkit-details-marker{display:none;}
  .summary-left{
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    gap:12px;
  }
  .tool-name{
    font-family:Georgia, serif;
    font-size:15.5px;
    color:var(--navy);
    font-weight:700;
  }
  .tool-tagline{
    font-size:12px;
    color:#8a8271;
    margin-top:2px;
  }
  .chevron{
    flex:0 0 auto;
    width:22px;
    height:22px;
    border-radius:50%;
    background:var(--cream);
    color:var(--navy);
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    justify-content:center;
    font-size:13px;
    transition:transform .15s ease;
  }
  details[open] .chevron{
    transform:rotate(45deg);
  }
  .body{
    padding:0 18px 20px;
    border-top:1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .field{
    margin-top:14px;
  }
  .field-label{
    font-size:10.5px;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    letter-spacing:.08em;
    color:var(--gold);
    font-weight:700;
    margin-bottom:4px;
  }
  .field-text{
    font-size:13.5px;
    color:var(--ink);
    line-height:1.55;
  }
  .field-text ol, .field-text ul{
    margin:6px 0 0;
    padding-left:18px;
  }
  .field-text li{
    margin-bottom:4px;
  }
  .badge-row{
    margin-top:14px;
    display:flex;
    gap:8px;
    flex-wrap:wrap;
  }
  .badge{
    font-size:11px;
    background:var(--navy);
    color:var(--cream);
    padding:4px 10px;
    border-radius:12px;
    font-weight:700;
  }
  .footer-note{
    margin-top:40px;
    padding:20px 22px;
    background:var(--navy);
    color:var(--cream);
    border-radius:6px;
    font-size:13px;
    line-height:1.5;
  }
  .footer-note strong{
    color:var(--gold-light);
  }
  .page-footer{
    margin-top:26px;
    padding-top:18px;
    border-top:2px solid var(--navy);
    font-family:Georgia, serif;
    color:var(--navy);
    font-weight:700;
    font-size:14px;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page">

  <div class="eyebrow">AgentHubTX</div>
  <h1>Help &amp; How-To</h1>
  <p class="intro">A quick reference for every tool on the hub — what it does, when to reach for it, and how to use it. Tap a tool to expand.</p>
  <p class="search-hint">Can't find what you're looking for, or something's not working? Check with your designated supervisor first.</p>

  <!-- ============ CORE COMPLIANCE ============ -->
  <div class="group-title">Core Compliance</div>

  <details id="my-iabs">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">My IABS</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Your personal, pre-filled Information About Brokerage Services form</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">Generates your own scoped IABS disclosure, pre-filled with your name and license info, ready to send or print for a client.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">At first substantive contact with any buyer or seller — this is a TREC requirement, not optional paperwork.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Open My IABS from the hub Tools menu</li>
            <li>Confirm your info is correct (it should auto-populate)</li>
            <li>Download or send the link directly to your client</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details id="client-ai-disclosure">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Client AI Disclosure</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Discloses AI-assisted content to clients where required</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">Generates a client-facing disclosure statement whenever AI has been used to help draft something they'll see — descriptions, emails, or offer analysis.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">Any time you use an EzzAgent Tool (or any AI tool) to produce content a client will read. This keeps you aligned with ABS's AI Use Policy.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Open Client AI Disclosure from the Tools menu</li>
            <li>Enter your PIN when prompted</li>
            <li>Attach or send the generated disclosure alongside the AI-assisted content</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="badge-row"><span class="badge">PIN required</span></div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ============ EZZAGENT TOOLS ============ -->
  <div class="group-title">EzzAgent Tools</div>

  <details id="listing-description">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Listing Description</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">AI-generated listing copy, TREC-safe by default</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">Writes a polished listing description from the property details you provide, avoiding language that could raise fair housing or disclosure issues.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">Any time you're prepping a new listing for MLS or marketing and want a clean first draft fast.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Enter the property's key details (beds, baths, features, neighborhood highlights)</li>
            <li>Generate the description</li>
            <li>Review and edit before publishing — always read it yourself first</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details id="client-email">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Client Email</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Draft client-facing emails in a professional, consistent voice</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">Generates a draft email for common client communications — status updates, showing follow-ups, closing reminders.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">When you know what you need to say but want a faster, cleaner starting point than a blank inbox.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Select the type of email and add a few specifics</li>
            <li>Generate the draft</li>
            <li>Personalize before sending — never send it unread</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details id="offer-strength">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Offer Strength</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Quick read on how a buyer's offer stacks up</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">Analyzes the terms of an offer (price, contingencies, financing, timeline) and gives you a plain-language breakdown of its relative strength.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">When you're helping a seller compare multiple offers, or want a sanity check on a buyer's offer before presenting it.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Enter the offer terms</li>
            <li>Review the generated breakdown</li>
            <li>Use it as a talking-point aid — not a substitute for your own judgment or legal advice</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details id="open-house-followup">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Open House Follow-Up</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Turn open house sign-ins into a follow-up sequence</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">Generates a follow-up message sequence for people who visited your open house, so no lead goes cold from forgetting to reach back out.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">The same day as your open house, while visitor details are still fresh.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Enter visitor names and notes from your sign-in sheet</li>
            <li>Generate the follow-up messages</li>
            <li>Send within 24 hours for best response rates</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details id="property-scout">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Property Scout</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Fast property research for a new address</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">Pulls together key property details to give you a quick research summary before a showing or listing appointment.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">Before a first showing or listing consultation, when you want to walk in already informed.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Enter the property address</li>
            <li>Review the summary generated</li>
            <li>Also available in ABS Field Tools for use on your phone in the field</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details id="buyer-intake">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Buyer Intake</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Capture new buyer info in one clean form</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">A structured intake form to capture a new buyer's needs, budget, and timeline in one place — feeds into your own records, not shared across agents.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">Your first meeting or call with a new buyer client.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Open Buyer Intake from Tools or the Field Tools app</li>
            <li>Fill in the client's details during or right after your conversation</li>
            <li>Reference it later when narrowing down listings for them</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ============ FIELD & FOLLOW-UP ============ -->
  <div class="group-title">Field &amp; Follow-Up</div>

  <details id="field-tools">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">ABS Field Tools (App)</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Property Scout + Buyer Intake, installable on your phone</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">A lightweight installable app version of Property Scout and Buyer Intake, built for use on your phone while you're out showing property.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">Anytime you're in the field without easy laptop access — at a showing, an open house, or between appointments.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Visit the Field Tools link on your phone's browser</li>
            <li>Tap "Add to Home Screen" to install it like an app</li>
            <li>Enter your PIN to access Property Scout and Buyer Intake</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="badge-row"><span class="badge">PIN required</span><span class="badge">Installable</span></div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details id="follow-up-tracker">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Follow-Up Tracker</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Keep leads warm with scheduled nurture reminders</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">Tracks your leads and reminds you when it's time to follow up, using templates so you're not writing from scratch every time.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">For any lead that isn't ready to transact today but shouldn't go cold — the majority of your pipeline.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Add a lead with their contact info and where they are in the process</li>
            <li>Choose or customize a follow-up template</li>
            <li>Check the tracker regularly — it only works if you act on the reminders</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ============ GETTING STARTED ============ -->
  <div class="group-title">Getting Started</div>

  <details id="onboarding-checklist">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Onboarding Checklist</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Your step-by-step path through AgentHubTX's tools</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What it does</div>
        <div class="field-text">Walks new agents through every core AgentHubTX tool, tracking your progress as you go.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">When to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">Your first few weeks with ABS — but it stays available if you want a refresher later.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">How to use it</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Open the Onboarding Checklist from the hub</li>
            <li>Work through each lesson at your own pace</li>
            <li>Progress is saved automatically to your account</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ============ BEST PRACTICES ============ -->
  <div class="group-title">Best Practices</div>
  <p style="font-size:12px;color:#8a8271;margin:-4px 0 12px;font-style:italic;">Brokerage guidance from ABS — not TREC-sourced. See the FAQ Resource for TREC-specific compliance questions.</p>

  <details id="ai-tool-caution">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Using AI Tools Safely</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">What to watch for with ChatGPT and other general AI tools</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">Why it matters</div>
        <div class="field-text">General-purpose AI tools like ChatGPT aren't built with Texas real estate law or TREC form requirements in mind. They can generate language that unintentionally crosses into legal advice or misrepresents disclosure obligations.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What to do instead</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Use EzzAgent Tools first for anything client-facing — Listing Description, Client Email, and Offer Strength are built around TREC-compliant language for these exact situations</li>
            <li>If you use a general AI tool instead, always review the output yourself before it reaches a client — especially anything touching legal terms, contingencies, or disclosure language</li>
            <li>Use Client AI Disclosure any time AI-assisted content goes to a client</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details id="cybersecurity-basics">
    <summary>
      <div class="summary-left">
        <div>
          <div class="tool-name">Cybersecurity Basics</div>
          <div class="tool-tagline">Protecting client data on your accounts and devices</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chevron">+</div>
    </summary>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">Why it matters</div>
        <div class="field-text">Real estate transactions involve sensitive client financial and personal information, and agents are frequent targets for wire fraud and phishing schemes tied to closings.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="field">
        <div class="field-label">What to do</div>
        <div class="field-text">
          <ol>
            <li>Use two-factor authentication on your email, CRM, and transaction management accounts</li>
            <li>Use a password manager for unique passwords across every tool — not just email</li>
            <li>Never act on wiring instructions received only by email — verify by phone using a number you already have on file</li>
            <li>For the full walkthrough, including the exact verification script to use before a closing, see the Email Security Checklist resource on the hub</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </details>

  <div class="footer-note">
    <strong>Still stuck?</strong> This page covers the how — for the why behind a policy or a TREC requirement, check the FAQ. For anything this page doesn't answer, reach out to your designated supervisor first, before escalating further.
  </div>

  <div class="page-footer">AgentHubTX</div>


</div>

<script>
  function openAndScrollToHash() {
    const id = decodeURIComponent(window.location.hash.slice(1));
    if (!id) return;
    const el = document.getElementById(id);
    if (!el || el.tagName.toLowerCase() !== 'details') return;

    el.open = true;
    el.classList.add('highlight');
    setTimeout(() => {
      el.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' });
    }, 50);
    setTimeout(() => el.classList.remove('highlight'), 2500);
  }

  window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', openAndScrollToHash);
  window.addEventListener('hashchange', openAndScrollToHash);
</script>
</body>
</html>
